HEADWORD: Scutiped
<hw>Scu"ti*ped</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>scutum</ets> a shield + <ets>pes</ets>, <ets>pedis</ets>, a foot:
cf. F. <ets>scutip⟦egrave⟧de</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>Having the anterior surface of the tarsus covered with scutella, or
transverse scales, in the form of incomplete bands terminating at a
groove on each side; -- said of certain birds.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

